Molar volume (Vm) indicates a spatial distribution of oxygen (O) atoms in the glass network. The molar volume of the samples decreased with an increase in Eu2O3 content and an increase in the density values. This subsequent change in ‘Vm’ is a normal behaviour expected in glass systems. The steady reduction in the ‘Vm’ values is attributed to the dense nature of the glass network. The number of bonds per unit volume (nb) values in Table 2 shows that nb increases with an increase in Eu2O3 [24]. The nb can be calculated by3nb=NAVm∑incxi\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
