According to Fajan’s rule, given in Dimitrov et al. [35], the polarizability of cation increases in the Coulomb field of the anion with an increase in its positive charge. As per the theory, in the condensed state of a matter, the charge distribution of each negative or positive ion can be distorted by the nearby another ion. That is, the polarizability or the loosening or tightening of the electron clouds entirely depends upon chemical binding forces. Hence, the αo2-n\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
